snippet.textDisplay:
distance between transistors 10 atoms wide actual transistors themselves much bigger for example a TSMC N7FF Transistor Gate Pitch is 54nm and its Minimum (metal) pitch is 40nm a transistor is those two parts wedged together as opposing spikes with some other materials in between so the actual minimum height of the transistor is somewhere less then 94nm but surely larger then 70nm however often transistors are deliberately made taller in order to achieve higher frequency's with worse current leak this is usually whats happening when a plus node come out 14nm++ is a taller spiky higher clocking less efficient version of 14nm

more rounded transistors use less current but taller transistors reach higher frequency if the 2nm node is 28% the size of the 7nm node then maybe transistors could be made as small as 20nm tall and like 8nm wide and 2nm apart but i guess only TSMC knows until someone takes a new chip cuts it in half and sticks it into a expensive high end lab electron microscope at some university somewhere
